UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426689900186
AB  - In light of Vogt's (1989) comment on our original paper, we reexamine the empirical evidence on how banks use reserve carryover. We dispute Vogt's characterization of the evidence as ‘contradictory’, and find nothing in the results to undermine our original conclusion that banks use the reserve carryover provision primarily to hedge reserves costs over time. We also correct a computational error that appeared in the original paper.
ER  - 

